=== Test 1: Auto-destroy without custom delete ===
Outer1.new
  Inner1.new(1)
Before function exit
  Inner1.delete(1)
After helper returned

=== Test 2: __new initializes defaults before user's new() ===
WithDefaults.new: a=10, b=20, setting c=30
Final: a=10, b=20, c=30

=== Test 3: Destruction order (reverse of declaration) ===
OrderedContainer.new
  OrderedField.new('first')
  OrderedField.new('second')
  OrderedField.new('third')
Before function exit
OrderedContainer.delete (user)
  OrderedField.delete('third')
  OrderedField.delete('second')
  OrderedField.delete('first')
After helper returned

=== Test 4: Shared<T> field auto-destruction ===
HoldsShared.new
  RefCountedData.new(42)
  RefCountedData.delete(42)
  ref_count after construction: 1
Before function exit
  RefCountedData.delete(42)
After helper - RefCountedData should be deleted

=== Test 5: Nested auto-destruction (3 levels) ===
Before function exit
Level1.delete(1)
  Level2.delete(10)
    Level3.delete(100)
After helper returned

=== Test 6: Optional<Shared<T>> field auto-destruction ===
HoldsOptionalShared.new
  OptionalData.new(99)
  OptionalData.delete(99)
  ref_count: 1
Before function exit (with value)
  OptionalData.delete(99)
After helper - OptionalData should be deleted
Before function exit (null)
After null helper - no crash expected

=== Test 7: Optional<T> with direct struct ===
HoldsOptionalDirect.new
  DirectStruct.new(77)
Before function exit
  DirectStruct.delete(77)
After helper - DirectStruct should be deleted

=== Test 8: Both __new and __delete on same struct ===
BothLifecycles.new: default_val=999
  Inner1.new(88)
Before function exit
  Inner1.delete(88)
After helper returned

=== Test 9: Multiple local variables destruction order ===
  TrackedVar.new('first')
  TrackedVar.new('second')
  TrackedVar.new('third')
Before function exit - destroys in reverse declaration order
  TrackedVar.delete('third')
  TrackedVar.delete('second')
  TrackedVar.delete('first')
After helper returned

=== Test 10: Temporary cleanup (no leaks) ===
--- fn call arg ---
  TrackedVar.new('fn-arg')
  TrackedVar.copy('fn-arg')
  TrackedVar.delete('fn-arg')
after consume(make())
--- nested fn call arg ---
  TrackedVar.new('nested')
  TrackedVar.copy('nested')
  TrackedVar.copy('nested')
  TrackedVar.delete('nested')
after consume(identity(make()))
--- orphaned fn call ---
  TrackedVar.new('orphan-fn')
after orphaned make()
--- orphaned construct expr ---
  TrackedVar.new('orphan-construct')
after orphaned TrackedVar construct
--- if expr as fn arg ---
  TrackedVar.new('if-true')
  TrackedVar.copy('if-true')
  TrackedVar.delete('if-true')
after consume(if ...)
  TrackedVar.delete('if-true')
  TrackedVar.delete('orphan-construct')
  TrackedVar.delete('orphan-fn')
  TrackedVar.delete('nested')
  TrackedVar.delete('nested')
  TrackedVar.delete('fn-arg')
All tests completed!
